  "author_association": "NONE",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "It seems that even `constant` functions are subject to the default gas limit (and probably also to the block gas limit, but I did not test that). This does not make sense to me. On my local node I should be able to spam myself as much as I choose to. If we waived the gas limit for constant functions, I could e.g. iterate arbitrarily long arrays. \r\n\r\nEDIT: I know that for iterating long random data I should probably rather use events and logs. But that would limit it to the access from the same contract which is fairly limiting.",
